# PC-Gaming

This Input.ini file was created by changing the settings in-game, within Descent Underground.
To use it, you will need to replace the current Input.ini file, located in your user folder within Windows. (path below)

Location of the Input.ini file on Windows 7/8/10: %UserProfile%\AppData\Local\Descent\Saved\Config\WindowsNoEditor

To use the Input.ini file... 
1. Install Descent Underground on Steam.
2. Run the game once to make sure it adds all of the correct files/folders.
3. Close the game.
4. Copy the text in my Input.ini file into your own Input.ini file (Located in this location: %UserProfile%\AppData\Local\Descent\Saved\Config\WindowsNoEditor)
5. Save your Input.ini file.
6. Close the text editor.
7. Run the game. You should now be able to play the game with this keyboard-only configuration.
